The paper discusses the implementation of network slicing in 5G communication systems, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the Service Level Agreement (SLA) between the tenant and service provider, which involves the management of resources and the allocation of services. This topic is related to Information Theory (cs.IT), as it deals with the transmission and processing of information. The paper also discusses the security and reliability of the network, which is related to Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the metrics of slice-based network SLA, which is related to Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Computer Engineering (cs.CE).
